        "text": "What explains a history? Nothing but itself, one had answered to this question not long ago and therefore distinguished a historical knowledge from a theoretical knowledge. Historical knowledge narrates singularities, theoretical knowledge explains events from the pattern of a reproduction that can be generalized for further cases. In this constellation there was a clever reserve, because in this way theoretical drafts and historical reality could be distinguished from each other and one could be warned against too quick confusion of one with the other. "
