        "id": "8344b636ece3bdbb",
        "text": "With all this, storytelling loses an innocence that it never had in truth. It becomes a narrative that contains a structure, the pattern of a repeatability, whose fascination consists in the fact that it is preserved even in the medium of singularities. And cultural studies becomes the narrative of narratives, the retelling of stories, which are characterized not least by the fact that stories are also told in them. Cultural studies becomes theoretical by asking about the constitutive role of storytelling in the repetition of particular stories. There were times when this was called ideology critique. Today, one experiments with various conceptual deployments, ranging from process to network to system or even \"field**, signaling that one can no longer be so sure of a philosophy of history that could back an ideology critique.\n"
